### Typography Rules

- **Primary UI text**: `font-family: var(--font-family)` (Inter Medium), `font-size: var(--font-size-sm)` (13px), `font-weight: var(--font-weight-medium)` (500), `line-height: var(--leading-sm)` (16px).
- **Display/headings**: `font-family: var(--font-family-display)` (Inter Display SemiBold), `font-size: var(--font-size-lg)` (17px).
- All UI text in the sidebar, top bar, tables, buttons uses the primary UI text style (13px/medium).

## Component Architecture

- **One folder per component** at `src/components/{ComponentName}/`.
- Each folder contains:
  - `{ComponentName}.tsx` вҖ” the React component
  - `{ComponentName}.module.css` вҖ” CSS Module styles
  - `icons.tsx` вҖ” component-specific icons (if needed)
  - `index.ts` вҖ” barrel export (re-exports the component and its types)
- Component names are PascalCase and must match the Figma component name.
- All components are exported from the root `src/index.ts`.

## Styling Approach

- Use **CSS Modules** (`*.module.css`) for component styles.
- Reference design tokens via `var(--token-name)` вҖ” never hardcode colors, spacing, or typography values.
- Support `dark` and `light` variants via CSS class modifiers (e.g., `.dark`, `.light`) when the Figma design has both modes.
- Transitions use `var(--transition-fast)` or `var(--transition-normal)`.

