## Two-Pass Spacing System

Every component goes through **two spacing passes** during creation. Pass 1 handles how the component relates to its surroundings. Pass 2 handles how elements inside the component breathe. Both must pass before a component is considered complete.

### Pass 1: General Spacing (Layout Context)

General spacing governs how a component sits within a page вҖ” the whitespace *around* it that gives the layout its rhythm. These rules apply when placing components on pages or in the playground.

#### Vertical Rhythm (Section Flow)

| Context | Token | Value | When to use |
|---------|-------|-------|-------------|
| Page top padding | `--space-6` | 24px | Top of any page content area |
| Page side padding | `--space-6` | 24px | Left/right of page content |
| Section gap (major) | `--space-10` | 40px | Between top-level content sections on a page |
| Section gap (within card) | `--space-8` | 32px | Between settings cards, card groups |
| Section heading вҶ’ content | `--space-4` | 16px | Below a section heading, before its first child |
| Section heading вҶ’ description вҶ’ content | heading 2px desc, desc 16px content | | When section has both heading and description |
| Card group gap | `--space-6` | 24px | Between sibling cards in a flex row |

#### Horizontal Rhythm (Sibling Flow)

| Context | Token | Value | When to use |
|---------|-------|-------|-------------|
| Tight inline siblings | `--space-2` | 8px | Buttons in a row, badges, small controls |
| Normal inline siblings | `--space-3` to `--space-4` | 12вҖ“16px | Form fields side by side, toggle + label |
| Spacious inline siblings | `--space-6` | 24px | Cards side by side, variant groups |
| Column gap (split layout) | `--space-8` | 32px | Inner body вҶ” Overview panel |

#### Component Placement Rules

- **Inputs, Selects, Textareas** default to `width: 100%` вҖ” they fill their container. The container controls the width.
- **Cards** have no outer margin by default вҖ” use the page/section gap to space them.
- **Buttons** in a row use `--space-2` (8px) gap.
- **Form groups** (label + input pairs) stack with `--space-4` (16px) gap between groups.
- **Label вҶ’ input** gap within a form group is `--space-1` (4px).
- **TopBar** provides its own internal padding (`--space-6` horizontal). No additional margin needed.
- **Dividers** replace margin between zones вҖ” when a divider separates two zones, each zone provides its own internal padding rather than relying on margin above/below the divider.

### Pass 2: Internal Spacing (Component Anatomy)

Internal spacing governs how elements *within* a component are padded, gapped, and aligned. This is what makes a component feel tight and intentional vs. loose and sloppy.

#### Container Padding

| Component type | Padding | Token | Notes |
|----------------|---------|-------|-------|
| Card | 12px vertical, 16px horizontal | `--space-3` / `--space-4` | Each zone (header, content, footer) gets its own padding |
| Dialog / Modal | 24px all sides | `--space-6` | Generous breathing room |
| Dropdown / Menu | 4px | `--space-1` | Tight padding around item list |
| Menu item | 6px vertical, 8px horizontal | `--space-1-5` / `--space-2` | Per-item hit area |
| Toast | 12px | `--space-3` | Compact notification |
| Input | 0 vertical, 8вҖ“12px horizontal | `--space-2` / `--space-3` | Height is set by size variant, horizontal padding varies |
| Badge | 2px vertical, 8px horizontal | 2px / `--space-2` | Pill shape, tight |
| Button | varies by size | see Button spec | sm=8px, default=6px/10px, lg=16px horizontal |

#### Internal Gaps

| Relationship | Gap | Token | Notes |
|-------------|-----|-------|-------|
| Icon вҶ” text (inline) | 6px | `--space-1-5` | Button icon+label, menu item icon+label |
| Title вҶ” description | 2вҖ“4px | `--space-0-5` to `--space-1` | Card header, dialog header, form section |
| Label вҶ” input | 4px | `--space-1` | Form groups |
| Toggle вҶ” label | 8px | `--space-2` | Switch + label pairs |
| Avatar вҶ” text | 8вҖ“12px | `--space-2` to `--space-3` | Profile rows, user mentions |
| Stacked text lines | 2px | `--space-0-5` | Name + role, title + subtitle |
| List items (vertical) | 2вҖ“4px | `--space-0-5` to `--space-1` | Menu items, nav items, select items |
| Checkbox/radio вҶ” label | 8px | `--space-2` | Inline check + text |
| Badge вҶ” badge (inline) | 4вҖ“6px | `--space-1` to `--space-1-5` | Tag rows |
| Footer buttons | 8px | `--space-2` | Dialog footer, card footer |

#### Zone Separation

Components with distinct visual zones (header, content, footer) use **border separators** instead of margin-based spacing:

| Pattern | Separator | Zone padding |
|---------|-----------|-------------|
| Card: header / content / footer | `1px solid --border-subtle` | Each zone: `--space-3` vertical, `--space-4` horizontal |
| Dialog: header / body / footer | No separator (margin only) | HeaderвҶ’footer: `--space-4` margin-top on footer |
| Drawer: header / content / footer | `1px solid --border-subtle` | Header/footer: 16px vert, 24px horiz |
| Settings card: title / body | `1px solid --border-subtle` | Title: 12px top, 16px sides. Body: 12px top, 16px sides |

#### The 4px Grid Rule

All spacing values must land on the **4px grid**. Valid values from the token scale:

```
0 вҶ’ 1px вҶ’ 2px вҶ’ 4px вҶ’ 6px вҶ’ 8px вҶ’ 10px вҶ’ 12px вҶ’ 16px вҶ’ 20px вҶ’ 24px вҶ’ 32px вҶ’ 40px вҶ’ 48px
```

The only exceptions are `1px` (borders, dividers), `2px` (tight text gaps, stepper item gap), and `6px` (icon-text gap, skeleton row gap). Every other spacing value must be a multiple of 4.

#### Spacing Anti-Patterns (Never Do)

| Anti-pattern | Fix |
|-------------|-----|
| `margin: 0 0 20px` on a card | Use section gap on the parent container instead |
| `padding: 5px 7px` on a button | Snap to 4px grid: `4px 8px` or `6px 8px` |
| Nesting margin + padding for the same gap | Pick one: padding on the parent OR margin on the child |
| `gap: 0` between form fields | Minimum `--space-1` (4px) between any interactive siblings |
| Inline `style={{ margin }}` on a reusable component | Component controls its internal spacing; layout controls external spacing |

### Spacing Pass Checklist (per component)

Before marking any component as complete, verify:

**Pass 1 (General):**
- [ ] Component has no hardcoded outer margin (layout controls placement)
- [ ] When placed in a page/section, the surrounding gap matches the vertical/horizontal rhythm table
- [ ] Inputs/selects are `width: 100%` by default
- [ ] Sibling spacing (buttons, badges, cards) uses the correct gap tier

**Pass 2 (Internal):**
- [ ] Container padding matches the component type table
- [ ] All internal gaps use design tokens, not hardcoded px values
- [ ] Icon-to-text gap is 6px (`--space-1-5`)
- [ ] Title-to-description gap is 2вҖ“4px
- [ ] Label-to-input gap is 4px (`--space-1`)
- [ ] Zone separators use `--border-subtle` where applicable
- [ ] All values land on the 4px grid (with noted exceptions)
- [ ] No margin/padding nesting conflicts

