#### Settings Page Token Spec

| Layer          | Property    | Token / Value                                     |
|----------------|-------------|----------------------------------------------------|
| Outer body     | fill        | `--bg-subtle` (`#fafafa`)                          |
| Main body card | margin      | `--space-2` (8px) on 3 sides                       |
| Main body card | fill        | `--bg-base` (white)                                |
| Main body card | border      | `1px solid --border-subtle`                        |
| Main body card | radius      | `--radius-lg` (8px)                                |
| Inner body     | max-width   | 600px                                              |
| Inner body     | padding     | horiz `--space-6` (24px), vert `--space-4` (16px)  |
| Inner body     | gap         | `--space-8` (32px) between cards                   |

#### Settings Page Rules

- **No global SidebarNav** вҖ” the Settings page replaces the normal sidebar with a **Settings Sidebar** (`sidebar type=settings`). The outer shell background and card pattern remain the same.
- **TopBar** shows the current settings page title (e.g., "Workspace", "Users"). Single-level breadcrumb like Main pages. No action button in the TopBar.
- The **Settings Sidebar** is embedded INSIDE the main content card, to the LEFT of the content area, separated by a **vertical divider** (`type=fill`, 1px).
- **Main body is empty** вҖ” it only serves as the container for the Inner body.
- **Inner body** contains a vertical stack of **Settings Cards**, each with max-width 600px, centered horizontally.
- Cards are separated by `--space-8` (32px) gap.
- **Stack all setting groups vertically on the page** вҖ” never place cards side by side.

#### Settings Sidebar Spec

The Settings Sidebar is a specialized navigation component for configuration pages.

