## Button Component Spec

### Primary (Brand) Button

Used for the main CTA in each page (e.g., "Create", "Start").

| Property     | Value                                                      |
|-------------|-------------------------------------------------------------|
| Background  | `--button-brand` (#235524)                                  |
| Text        | `--fg-on-color` (white), 13px medium                        |
| Border      | `--shadow-button-primary` (1px #0d330d ring + drop shadow)  |
| Radius      | `--radius-sm` (4px)                                         |
| Inner glow  | `inset 0 0.75px 0 rgba(255,255,255,0.2)`                   |

**Size variants:**
- `sm`: height 24px, padding 8px horizontal.
- `default`: height auto, padding 6px vertical / 10px horizontal.

**Best practice** (from Figma spec):
- **Main pages**: Always use `Button variant=primary, size=sm` in the top right to create new items. If the page has no create functionality, hide this button entirely вҖ” do not render a disabled button.
- **Sub pages**: Always use `Button variant=secondary (neutral), size=sm` in the top right to edit items. If there is no edit functionality, remove this button entirely.
- **Inner pages**: Always use `Button variant=primary, size=sm` in the top right. Label is contextual: "Create" for new resources, "Save" or "Update" for editing existing ones.

### Neutral (Outline) Button

| Property     | Value                                                       |
|-------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Background  | `--button-neutral` (white)                                   |
| Text        | `--fg-base` (#18181b), 13px medium                           |
| Border      | `--shadow-button-neutral` (1px ring + drop shadow)           |
| Radius      | `--radius-sm` (4px)                                          |

