## Product Information

> **Sentra** вҖ” built and designed by **Shaurya Narang**.

When building UI, use **"Sentra"** for workspace names, branding, and placeholder text.

### Product Architecture (from Figma navigation)

| Area       | Pages                                                        |
|-----------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Home      | Dashboard / overview                                         |
| Inbox     | Notifications, messages, review requests                     |
| Quality   | Evaluations, Calibrations, Workflows, Reviews, Alerts, Reports |
| Training  | (Collapsible section вҖ” training-related pages)               |
| Hiring    | (Collapsible section вҖ” hiring-related pages)                 |
| Resources | Simulations, Scorecards, Personas, Backend Tools             |
| Settings  | Uses **Settings Page Template** (see below)                  |

**Settings sub-pages (from Settings Sidebar):**

| Section   | Pages                                                   |
|-----------|---------------------------------------------------------|
| General   | Workspace, Users, Groups, Audit logs, Agent voice guide |
| Quality   | Conversation flags, Calibrations, Processes             |
| Training  | Teams, Learner roles                                    |

### Page Hierarchy

The product has four page types, each with its own layout template:

1. **Main pages** вҖ” accessed directly from the sidebar (e.g., Evaluations list). Use the **Main Page Template** with Create button and optional tabs.
2. **Sub pages** вҖ” accessed by clicking a row on a main page (e.g., a specific Evaluation). Use the **Sub Page Template** with back breadcrumb, Edit button, Inner body + Overview panel.
3. **Inner pages** вҖ” accessed via "Create" or "Edit" actions from a Main or Sub page (e.g., creating a new Evaluation, editing a Scorecard). Use the **Inner Page Template** with a three-column layout: Page Sidebar (stepper nav) + Inner body (form sections) + Preview panel (read-only summary).
4. **Settings pages** вҖ” accessed from the global Settings item. Use the **Settings Page Template** with a Settings Sidebar (replacing the global SidebarNav) + card-based form content area. No action buttons in TopBar.

### Sub Page Content Pattern (example: Simulation detail)

The inner body shows multiple named sections stacked vertically:
- **"Simulations"** section вҖ” table with columns: Name, Difficulty, Language
- **"Flows"** section вҖ” table with columns: Name, Steps
- Gap of `--space-10` (40px) between sections

The overview panel shows metadata:
- Attempts: 3
- Manager: (avatar)
- Conversations: 18

This pattern applies to any resource detail page (Simulations, Scorecards, Personas, etc.).

### Inner Page Content Pattern (example: Evaluation creation)

The page sidebar uses a stepper navigation:
- **Setup** (active) вҶ’ **Filters** вҶ’ **Workflows** вҶ’ **Testing**
- Clicking a stepper item scrolls/navigates the Inner body to that section.

The inner body contains form sections:
- **"Setup"** section вҖ” form groups: Source (Select source), Scorecard (Select scorecard), Frequency (Select timeframe)
- **"Workflows"** section вҖ” description text + form group: Select (optional)
- Gap of `--space-10` (40px) between sections. Each section heading is 17px Inter Display SemiBold (`--font-family-display`).

The preview panel shows a read-only summary of configured values:
- Source: (avatar icon) Intercom вҖ” filled, `--fg-base`
- Scorecard: (avatar icon) Sales Performance вҖ” filled, `--fg-base`
- Filters: None applied вҖ” default, `--fg-disabled`
- Workflows: None applied вҖ” default, `--fg-disabled`
- --- (dotted divider) ---
- Conversations: n/a вҖ” below-divider group

This pattern applies to any resource creation/edit page (Evaluations, Scorecards, Simulations, etc.).

### Usage Notes
- Use this information when creating navigation structures, naming placeholder content, and building realistic sample data.
- Always use "Sentra" for all user-facing text, branding, and placeholder content.

