## Interaction Best Practices

> These rules are derived from the Figma "Best practices" documentation pages. They define **how** common UI actions should behave across Sentra. Follow them when building any interactive feature.

### Common Actions

#### Add

*Introduce new or existing content into the interface (placing an item in a list, inserting an element into a layout).*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Primary button for the most important action | Do | Use the primary (brand) button for the main "Create" action on a page |
| Plus icon for secondary add actions | Do | For outline and ghost button variants, default to the `+` (plus) icon вҖ” e.g., `+ Add`, `+ Add filter` |
| Ghost button for contextual add | Do | Add actions within a section (filter rows, tables) should use a ghost button variant |
| Add actions below scrollable lists | Do | Position `+ Add tool` below the list of selectable options, outside the scrollable area so it stays visible |
| No add at page bottom | Don't | Never place add actions at the very bottom of a page вҖ” they get lost |
| No intermediate creation steps | Don't | Don't show configuration dropdowns on the Create button. Navigate directly to the creation page (Inner Page Template) and let the user configure there |

#### Edit

*Modify content or objects that already exist.*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Outline button or outline icon button | Do | Edit actions use the `outline` button variant by default вҖ” choose between text button (`вңҸ Edit`) or icon-only button (`вңҸ`) depending on available space |
| PencilSimpleLine icon | Do | Always use the `PencilSimpleLine` icon for edit actions |
| Consolidate with More Actions | Don't | Don't place too many edit actions together. If there are multiple, use a More Actions (`вӢ®`) menu instead |

#### Delete

*Permanently erase an item or object from the system.*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Keep destructive button simple | Do | Use the plain destructive button variant вҖ” just "Delete" in red |
| Hide behind More Actions | Do | Delete should live inside a `вӢ®` menu (Edit / Duplicate / Delete) вҖ” not exposed as a standalone button |
| Icon button destructive variant | Do | When using an icon button, use the destructive variant |
| Trash icon in menus | Do | Use the trash icon (`TrashSimple`) for destructive menu items |
| Delete at end of menu | Don't | Never place Delete in the middle of a menu list вҖ” always last |
| No clashing primary buttons | Don't | Avoid pairing a destructive primary button with other primary buttons (e.g., Cancel + Delete + Save) |

**Deletion severity tiers:**

| Tier | When to use | UX pattern |
|------|-------------|------------|
| **Low-impact** | Easily reversible, data can be recreated quickly | Remove immediately on click. No confirmation dialog. |
| **Moderate-impact** | Irreversible or involves data that can't be easily restored. Also for bulk deletes. | Confirmation via **Alert Dialog** ("Are you sure you want to delete this team? This action is irreversible." вҶ’ Cancel / Delete) |
| **High-impact** | Permanently erases critical data (e.g., deleting an account) | User must **type the resource name** to confirm. Delete button disabled until text matches exactly. |

**Confirmation feedback:** Always show a **loading toast** ("Deleting item...") if slow, then a **success toast** ("Item deleted successfully") on completion.

#### Remove

*Disconnect or detach an item (does NOT permanently delete data).*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| X icon with ghost icon button | Do | Use the `X` icon with a ghost icon button for inline removals (filters, tags, chips) |
| No trash icon | Don't | Never use the trash/delete icon for Remove actions вҖ” trash means permanent deletion |

#### More Actions

*Show additional options for a page, element, or item.*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Vertical ellipsis icon (`вӢ®`) | Do | Use the vertical ellipsis to indicate more actions are available |
| Position at end of group | Do | More Actions goes LAST вҖ” after all other visible actions (e.g., `Export` | `Create` | `вӢ®`) |

#### Copy

*Duplicate selected content to the user's clipboard.*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Ghost icon button + clipboard icon | Do | For text copy actions (copy a value, copy an ID) |
| Outline icon button + link icon | Do | For copying deep links or URLs |
| Outline button with dropdown | Do | When copy has multiple options (e.g., "Copy link в–ҫ" вҶ’ Copy admin link / Copy agent link) |
| Show on hover in tables | Do | Copy icon appears on row hover вҖ” use ghost icon button variant |
| Confirmation toast | Do | Always show an **info toast** ("Link copied to your clipboard") after copying |

#### Duplicate

*Create a new copy of content within the system, leaving the original unchanged.*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Ghost icon button + copy icon | Do | For item duplication actions |
| **Duplicating items** | вҖ” | Creates copy directly in the same view. Quick and immediate. |
| **Duplicating pages** | вҖ” | Takes a few seconds. Opens the new copy in a separate tab to avoid disrupting current flow. |
| Confirmation toast | Do | Loading ("Duplicating...") вҶ’ Success ("Item duplicated successfully") or Error ("Unable to duplicate. Please try again.") |

---

### Visual Guidelines

#### Button Hierarchy

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Primary + secondary for main view | Do | Use primary (brand) and secondary (outline) button variants to guide users вҖ” primary for the most likely action |
| Ghost icon buttons for list items | Do | Use ghost icon button variant for per-item/per-row actions in tables and lists (e.g., `вӢ®` at end of each row) |
| Max 2 filled/shaped buttons | Don't | Never place more than two filled or shaped buttons in a single section вҖ” it disrupts visual hierarchy |

---

### Content Guidelines

#### Naming

Names influence how users perceive and understand the product. A well-chosen name should:
- Put clarity above creativity
- Help establish a mental model for our audiences
- Enhance people's perception of our brand
- Increase adoption of the product or feature
- Clarify where a product or feature fits into the Sentra brand system

The naming process involves collaboration вҖ” include different disciplines and subject matter expertise.

#### Date and Time

| Recency | Format | Example |
|---------|--------|---------|
| < 7 days | Relative with minutes (m), hours (h), days (d) | `1h ago`, `3d ago` |
| вүҘ 7 days | Absolute: `MMM DD, YYYY` | `Dec 2, 2025` |

#### Accessibility

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Card descriptions | Do | Use description text for cards **only** when necessary to provide additional context |
| Truncated text | Do | If text is truncated, show the full text on hover in a **tooltip** |

---

### Layout / Ordering

*Each action should have a clear purpose, illustrated through a text label, an icon, or both.*

| Rule | Type | Detail |
|------|------|--------|
| Primary action goes LAST | Do | Place the primary (brand) button as the rightmost action вҖ” e.g., `Export` (outline) then `Edit` (primary) |
| No same-variant side by side | Don't | Never place two buttons of the same variant next to each other (e.g., two primary buttons) |
| iconButton for secondary/destructive | Do | Use an iconButton (`вӢ®`) to store secondary actions, especially destructive ones вҖ” place it at the very end |
| Dividers separate button groups | Do | Use a vertical divider component to visually separate groups of related buttons (e.g., `[icon Select в–ҫ]` | `[в–Ҫ Filter]`) |

