## Icon Library

> Complete catalog of icons from the Figma design system in **two styles**: Outline (stroke) and Fill (solid). Standard icon frame is **15Г—15px**. Use the kebab-case name as the icon identifier when referencing in code.

### Icon Framing Spec

| Property | Outline | Fill |
|----------|---------|------|
| Style | Stroke-based (transparent fill) | Solid-filled shapes |
| Frame size | 15Г—15px | 15Г—15px |
| Stroke width | 1.5px (standard), 1px (mini) | N/A (paths are filled) |
| Color | Inherits `currentColor` | Inherits `currentColor` |
| Grid | 6 icons per row in Figma | 6 icons per row in Figma |
| When to use | Default for UI chrome, buttons, nav | Active/selected states, status indicators, emphasis |

**Naming convention:** Fill icons append `-solid` or `-filled` to the outline name (e.g., `star` вҶ’ `star-solid`, `house` вҶ’ `house-filled`). Some fill-only icons have no outline counterpart.

### Icon Variants

Some icons have size variants indicated by suffix:
- **(no suffix)** вҖ” Standard 15Г—15px, 1.5px stroke
- **`-mini`** вҖ” Compact variant, typically used inline with text (12Г—12px visual area)
- **`-micro`** вҖ” Smallest variant, used for tight UI (10Г—10px visual area)

